body: Naseem Tarawnah reflects on leadership changes in Tunisia and its potential impact on Jordan. "Today, Jordan, and perhaps much of the Arab world is learning one important lesson from Tunisia: the call for political change from the domestic constituency is unlikely to happen in the region unless the economy gets bad, real, real, bad."

title: Jordan: Reflections on Tunisia
